messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
My girlfriend was raped and I think she's dead.
I need someone here now.
Okay. Is she breathing?
No, she isn't. There's vomit. She's been beaten.
There's something tied around her neck. I just cut it off. She's dead.
I've been doing CPR for the past 20 minutes. She ain't coming back.
What's your address?
Yes, it's called Cambridge Square. The complex.
Someone said they already called an ambulance, but I'm just making sure.
Who called the ambulance?
My neighbors.
Okay, we don't have a call on it. You said you've been doing CPR?
Yeah. Get someone down here right now before I kill them.
They're on their way, okay?
Because I think my neighbor did it.
I've got another dispatcher dispatching them at this time. Do you want to continue to try to do CPR?
Yes.
Tell me what I need to do.
Are you there?
Yes.
Okay, you're going to take your hands and place them in the center of her chest, right between the nipples.
All right.
Push down hard and fast, about two inches in depth, and do it about 100 times a minute.
Say that again.
You're going to do about 100 compressions per minute, very quickly paced.
Do it 100 times on her chest? That's what you're saying?
Yes, keep doing that. Do 30 compressions, then give her two breaths.
One, two, three... okay, 30. Now tilt her head back and give her two breaths?
Yes, and then continue with 30 more compressions.
It doesn't seem like air's coming out, but I'll keep doing it.
Keep doing it. 30 more compressions, and then two more breaths.
30 more compressions. Two more breaths. Okay.
She sounds like she's choking with vomit. I can tell she's vomited.
There's bruises all around her neck. She doesn't have a pulse.
Okay, keep doing compressions.
Please, God. I'll get to 30. Two more breaths again.
9-1-1, I think we got disconnected.
Sorry.
That's okay. Are you still doing the compressions?
Yes. My girlfriend's been raped. She's dead.
Sir, are you still doing CPR?
Yes, I'm doing CPR.
Who's there with you?
My neighbor.
Come on, baby.
You're doing just fine, okay?
Give her the two breaths.
Okay, take the phone and talk to this lady.
Hello?
Hello. Do you know how old she is?
She's 17, I think.
Okay, keep going, don't stop. Help is on the way.
Yeah, he's doing it. He's trying to bring her back.
He found her like this?
Yes.
Okay. Is he following the instructions I gave?
Yeah, he's doing just what you said.
Is the door unlocked so the crews can come inside?
Yes, they're on their way up now.
Okay, they should be there any moment.
Yes, they're here.
I'm still here.
The ambulance is here. They're inside the apartment.
Okay, stay on the line until they take over.
I can't believe it. My girlfriend is dead.
Are you still on the phone?
Yes, I am.
Are you still there?
Yes, we're still here.
